that she can have two more hours.

26
00:01:46,639 --> 00:01:48,199
She can come back later.

27
00:01:48,199 --> 00:01:48,760
Your Majesty.

28
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:49,919
But why?

29
00:01:49,919 --> 00:01:51,559
I never saw this sickness coming.

30
00:01:51,559 --> 00:01:53,319
I don't want to worry her.

31
00:01:54,199 --> 00:01:54,839
Your Majesty.

32
00:01:56,519 --> 00:01:57,279
(Xuan,)

33
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,680
(you're so nice to me.)

34
00:02:00,519 --> 00:02:01,680
Shen Ao, get out of my sight now.

35
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,199
I don't want to see you here anymore.

36
00:02:03,199 --> 00:02:03,959
You're dismissed.

37
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:05,319
Yes, Your Majesty.

38
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:09,679
Is she gone yet?

39
00:02:13,839 --> 00:02:15,000
How was my acting?

40
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:15,960
It was amazing.

41
00:02:19,318 --> 00:02:22,360
[Xuanchen Hall]

42
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,000
Shen Ao.

43
00:02:23,199 --> 00:02:23,960
Wait a minute.

44
00:02:24,479 --> 00:02:25,520
How can I be of help, Your Majesty?

45
00:02:25,919 --> 00:02:26,679
Tell me the truth.

46
00:02:26,679 --> 00:02:27,960
I'm ready to hear it.

47
00:02:28,119 --> 00:02:29,080
Tell you about what?

48
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:30,960
I heard it all from the outside.

49
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:32,399
What is His Majesty's diagnosis?

50
00:02:32,479 --> 00:02:33,160
Your Majesty.

51
00:02:33,479 --> 00:02:35,320
His Majesty doesn't want to worry you.

52
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:36,479
I'm already feeling worried.

53
00:02:36,479 --> 00:02:37,160
Just tell me.

54
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:38,399
Otherwise, don't think about leaving.

55
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:40,199
Fine. Your Majesty.

56
00:02:40,479 --> 00:02:42,440
I'll tell you the truth.

57
00:02:43,039 --> 00:02:44,279
His Majesty has always suffered from asthma
since he was a kid.

58
00:02:44,479 --> 00:02:46,119
Every time His Majesty
catches a cold, skips meals,

59
00:02:46,399 --> 00:02:48,440
or doesn't get enough rest, he will get phlegm.

60
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:50,000
The phlegm will then block his airways.

61
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,279
Eventually, his lungs get fatigued

62
00:02:51,639 --> 00:02:52,639
and His Majesty will struggle
with shortness of breath.

63
00:02:52,759 --> 00:02:55,639
You can even hear the wheezing
when it gets severe.

64
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:57,039
It sounds just like this.

65
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:05,000
Can you put it plainly?

66
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:07,759
All in all, it won't cost His Majesty his life,
but it is a serious matter.

67
00:03:07,759 --> 00:03:08,720
His Majesty will suffer.

68
00:03:09,559 --> 00:03:10,800
Suffer?

69
00:03:11,119 --> 00:03:12,360
You can't let that happen.
You're the imperial physician, aren't you?

70
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,440
You have to help him.

71
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:14,720
To tell you the truth,

72
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:17,119
I've developed a special medicine recently.

73
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:19,839
One dose is enough to relieve the symptoms.

74
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,559
If His Majesty can drink it
for 21 consecutive days,

75
00:03:21,559 --> 00:03:22,800
he'll be completely cured.

76
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,479
Unfortunately,

77
00:03:25,279 --> 00:03:26,399
when I was developing the medicine,

78
00:03:26,559 --> 00:03:27,919
I tested it on many people in the palace.

79
00:03:28,479 --> 00:03:30,199
His Majesty thought it was unethical

80
00:03:30,399 --> 00:03:31,679
and stubbornly refused to take the medicine.

81
00:03:32,039 --> 00:03:32,759
I see.

82
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:35,039
He did say that you were inhuman.

83
00:03:35,279 --> 00:03:36,440
But you were only testing the medicine.

84
00:03:36,559 --> 00:03:37,160
It isn't a big deal, is it?

85
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:38,399
You may not know, Your Majesty,

86
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,080
but this medicine

87
00:03:41,199 --> 00:03:43,119
fights poison with poison.

88
00:03:43,399 --> 00:03:44,279
Take this once a day.

89
00:03:44,279 --> 00:03:45,000
One drop at a time.

90
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:47,080
Overdosing on this will affect your health.

91
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,440
Can you be more specific?

92
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:49,440
How deadly is this?

93
00:03:49,639 --> 00:03:51,559
It depends.

94
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,880
Whoever finishes the entire bottle in one go

95
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:57,000
will lose his or her life.

96
00:03:58,320 --> 00:03:59,479
It's really deadly.

97
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,839
Are you sure it's fine to take a drop of this?

98
00:04:01,839 --> 00:04:02,880
It's absolutely fine.

99
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:04,000
Don't worry, Your Majesty.

100
00:04:05,639 --> 00:04:07,399
Fine.

101
00:04:07,839 --> 00:04:08,839
Leave this to me.

102
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:11,720
One drop at a time. Never more than that.

103
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:12,759
Overdose is fatal.

104
00:04:12,759 --> 00:04:13,960
One drop at a time. Never more than that.

105
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:14,880
Never more than that.

106
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:15,600
One drop at a time.

107
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:16,839
You can't take the entire bottle at one go.

108
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:24,440
Your Majesty.

109
00:04:24,559 --> 00:04:26,160
Is this enough?

110
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,399
No.

111
00:04:27,399 --> 00:04:28,119
The main ingredient

112
00:04:28,119 --> 00:04:29,359
of this cough-calming herbal soup is radish.

113
00:04:29,359 --> 00:04:30,239
Chop up more radishes.

114
00:04:30,839 --> 00:04:31,399
Now.

115
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:32,640
Your Majesty.

116
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:35,079
What made you want to cook soup all of a sudden?

117
00:04:35,079 --> 00:04:36,399
I'm making this for Xuan.

118
00:04:36,399 --> 00:04:37,880
I knew he is always a thin guy,

119
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:39,679
but I didn't know he'd get sick so easily.

120
00:04:39,799 --> 00:04:41,480
He has been suffering from this illness
since childhood.

121
00:04:42,519 --> 00:04:43,519
So you're cooking soup

122
00:04:43,519 --> 00:04:45,239
for His Majesty.

123
00:04:45,399 --> 00:04:46,760
Yes. Poor little one.

124
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:48,000
I have to take good care of him in the future.

125
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,799
Hurry up and prepare the radish.

126
00:04:49,799 --> 00:04:50,239
Sure.

127
00:04:50,239 --> 00:04:51,279
Get me some honey too.

128
00:04:51,279 --> 00:04:51,959
Honey?

129
00:04:51,959 --> 00:04:52,760
We ran out of honey.

130
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:54,600
I'll get some from the store.

131
00:04:55,119 --> 00:04:55,720
Go ahead.

132
00:05:23,799 --> 00:05:24,920
No way.

133
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,000
Are you sure she poured the entire bottle

134
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,160
into the soup?

135
00:05:28,239 --> 00:05:29,559
I saw it with my own eyes.

136
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:31,720
That's exactly what she did.

137
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,079
Fine.

138
00:05:33,679 --> 00:05:35,600
It's no doubt she's Scorpion Liu's daughter.

139
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,519
She's just as cruel.

140
00:05:37,119 --> 00:05:38,720
However, it seems to me

141
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:41,079
that Her Majesty cares for Your Majesty a lot.

142
00:05:41,079 --> 00:05:42,040
It was just an act.

143
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:44,640
I can't wait to see

144
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:47,119
how she will keep her act up.

145
00:05:51,839 --> 00:05:52,600
Xuan.

146
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:54,279
I cooked this especially for you.

147
00:05:54,279 --> 00:05:55,239
I spent an entire afternoon

148
00:05:55,239 --> 00:05:56,480
cooking this bowl of soup.

149
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:57,799
It contains all the essence of the ingredients.

150
00:05:58,040 --> 00:06:00,519
Why did you make me soup all of a sudden?

151
00:06:02,839 --> 00:06:03,640
You must be tired

152
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:04,959
from teaching me all the palace rules.

153
00:06:04,959 --> 00:06:05,760
I don't want you to overwork yourself,

154
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:06,959
so I thought I should cook soup for you.

155
00:06:07,799 --> 00:06:09,799
(You just want to kill me, right?)

156
00:06:13,399 --> 00:06:15,079
I'm doing fine. I'm not tired at all.

157
00:06:15,079 --> 00:06:16,079
I don't need this.

158
00:06:17,519 --> 00:06:18,920
You look tired. You...

159
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:20,839
Don't be shy.

160
00:06:20,839 --> 00:06:21,640
Drink it

161
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:22,399
while it's hot.

162
00:06:22,399 --> 00:06:24,239
(She's trying to force the poison down my throat.
How daring.)

163
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,040
You're so adorable.

164
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,119
Fine. I'll feed you.

165
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:35,519
Here.

166
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,119
Sorry, Jinfeng.

167
00:06:42,119 --> 00:06:43,160
It's my fault.

168
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:44,720
I've let you down.

169
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:47,399
It's fine.

170
00:06:47,399 --> 00:06:48,279
Don't beat yourself up.

171
00:06:48,279 --> 00:06:49,959
I'm sure you didn't mean it.

172
00:06:49,959 --> 00:06:51,720
I can cook you

173
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:52,839
a whole pot of this, Your Majesty.

174
00:06:52,839 --> 00:06:54,239
This is nothing.

175
00:06:54,519 --> 00:06:55,920
I'm just sad that we have to waste the soup.

176
00:06:56,079 --> 00:06:58,600
I'm sure you'll feel much better
after drinking this.

177
00:06:59,839 --> 00:07:01,279
(I might die here.)

178
00:07:01,279 --> 00:07:02,359
(How can this make me feel better?)

179
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,279
(She actually said these malicious words)

180
00:07:04,279 --> 00:07:05,959
(so nonchalantly.)

181
00:07:06,279 --> 00:07:07,880
(How brutal.)

182
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:10,399
I'm feeling much better now.

183
00:07:10,399 --> 00:07:12,399
I appreciate what you did for me.

184
00:07:12,399 --> 00:07:13,640
There will be plenty of chances in the future,

185
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:16,399
so I'll try your cooking next time.

186
00:07:16,799 --> 00:07:17,720
There is some soup left.

187
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:19,000
Why don't you finish them?

188
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,640
Why don't you drink it?

189
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:21,799
We're husband and wife.

190
00:07:21,799 --> 00:07:23,279
You can drink it on my behalf.

191
00:07:23,279 --> 00:07:24,480
No, I don't need it.

192
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:25,399
I'm very healthy.

193
00:07:25,399 --> 00:07:26,200
This is for you.

194
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,519
How dare you?

195
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,040
What's the matter?

196
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:32,079
You said I needed this.

197
00:07:32,079 --> 00:07:33,720
Do you take me as a dead man?

198
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:37,640
I think you need some vitality water.

199
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:39,399
I got this from Xianpa Village.

200
00:07:39,839 --> 00:07:41,600
Vitality water?

201
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,399
Vitality water is Xianpa Village's specialty.

202
00:07:43,399 --> 00:07:45,079
It's made with the spring water
on Xianpa Mountain

203
00:07:45,079 --> 00:07:46,720
and herbal extracts.

204
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:48,399
Drinking it can vitalize your body.

205
00:07:48,399 --> 00:07:50,160
My mother got this for me.

206
00:07:51,519 --> 00:07:53,839
Extend my gratitude to your mother.

207
00:07:54,079 --> 00:07:54,959
Of course.

208
00:07:54,959 --> 00:07:56,279
So why are you so upset?

209
00:07:59,519 --> 00:08:01,559
I've never liked

210
00:08:01,559 --> 00:08:02,959
others calling me weak.

211
00:08:02,959 --> 00:08:04,720
It makes me look bad.

212
00:08:05,959 --> 00:08:07,399
So this is why you're upset.

213
00:08:07,399 --> 00:08:08,679
You need to maintain your image
in front of others,

214
00:08:08,679 --> 00:08:09,839
but you need to take care of your health too.

215
00:08:09,839 --> 00:08:11,000
Drink it.

216
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:17,440
Why are you drinking it?

217
00:08:19,239 --> 00:08:21,040
It's getting cold.

218
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,200
It's not easy to heat this up.

219
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,359
I can't waste the good stuff.

220
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:25,559
But it's fine.

221
00:08:25,559 --> 00:08:26,399
Luckily, my mother is smart enough

222
00:08:26,399 --> 00:08:27,559
and get me an extra bottle.

223
00:08:30,959 --> 00:08:32,119
It's been a while since I last saw my mother.

224
00:08:32,119 --> 00:08:33,479
I wonder how she's doing.

225
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:34,880
Is she eating well?

226
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:36,159
Is she sleeping well?

227
00:08:36,159 --> 00:08:38,080
Has she caught the chicken thief?

228
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:40,520
You miss your mother?

229
00:08:41,640 --> 00:08:44,039
This is the longest
I have been without my mother by my side.

230
00:08:44,719 --> 00:08:46,440
My mother only wanted the best for me

231
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:48,440
when she kicked me out of the village
and sent me to my father.

232
00:08:48,599 --> 00:08:50,039
However, she didn't manage to attend my wedding.

233
00:08:51,359 --> 00:08:53,440
It seems like you have a very good relationship
with your mother.

234
00:08:53,679 --> 00:08:55,400
She's my mother.

235
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:56,280
Of course, we have a good relationship.

236
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:58,080
I don't know how that feels.

237
00:09:00,159 --> 00:09:01,679
My mother passed away at a young age,

238
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:04,640
but my father was very fond of me
when I was little.

239
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:08,679
I remember how my father always brought me
out of the palace

240
00:09:09,239 --> 00:09:11,640
